  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6577.87 sitting below the massive negative gamma wall at 6570 (-22.4B), dealers are likely buying the dip here as they're short gamma below this level, creating amplified downside momentum. The PIN regime and substantial positive gamma fortress from 6590-6600 (+41.2B at 6600 peak) suggests dealers will aggressively sell any rallies back toward these levels, capping upside. Key inflection point is the 6570 strike - a break below accelerates dealer buying and downside volatility, while a reclaim above 6590 hits the positive gamma stabilization zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile action with dealers defending the 6570 floor but capping rallies at 6590-6600.",
